column1: OSF | Wave 10.1 | ACC2 | OGW is calling search customer API for both MMO and MMC Market
column39:
*Steps to reproduce:*
 # Login to Retail/Telesales channel
 # Search customer on frontend

 

*Actual Result:*  OGW is calling search customer API for both MMO and MMC Market 

 

{*}Expected Result{*}:  OGW should not call search customer API for both MMO and MMC Market 

 
|If marketCode field is empty in request, then the following Service will be invoked|
|Protocol|Tuxedo|
|Operation|eaiGtMarket|
|Service|CSM145|

the reply is not correct in almost all topics as highlighted in already attached email in yellow the bpName is sent  <bas:bpName>CustomerAccount002:SearchCustomerBANSubscriber as seen in Tibco logs. BKS would be something for FixedNet but this is Mobile for Kias so 2. Is wrong and bpName has to be corrected for SoapAction used.

 

Concerning 1. OGW1758878870199 Tibco does not care how OSF is generating their bpId but the 2 separate invocations of the service first for MMC then for MMO each have to have a unique bpId, that is a operational requirement as shared to all developing parties using Tibco EAI/ESB. If the timestamp only has definition of seconds then this is not sufficient to being unique, but this has to be ensure by each client. OGW has to correct this !

 

If OSF/OGW is using boId same as bpId then they did not understand the purpose of those 2 parameters and have to read the specifications.

 

Finally doing same request for both marketCodes MMC and MMO does not make sense, any customer can only belong to one market. This violates the principal of avoiding unnecessary load on backends Tibco EAI and Kias. If OGW does not know the market of customer/BAN according to spec the parameter can be sent as empty and Tibco will check by eaiGtMarket first.
|Backend Interface|KIAS|If marketCode field is empty in request, then the following Service will be invoked|
|Protocol|Tuxedo|
|Operation|eaiGtMarket|
|Service|CSM145|
|CSM service to SearchCustomerBANSubscriber|
|Protocol|Tuxedo|
|Operation|eaiSrchCstBan|
|Service|CSM144|
column367: Size of the EAI logs is increasing, making unnecessary requests wastes backend resources and must be avoided.

column1: OSF | Wave10.1 | ACC2 | IT | Incorrect conditionServiceName passed in SOM logs for tariff promo ID P-0370-01-01
column39:
We have observed that for tariff promo ID {*}P-0370-01-01{*}, conditionServiceName value is passed correctly as *GS_Glas_9x25E[br]* for Barcode *VDE7730015271* from the OGW but while the Barcode is passing through POS to backend systems the value is passed as *?* instead of actual value *GS_Glas_9x25E[br]* in SOM logs in IT env.

 

*Steps to Reproduce:*

1) Login Omnius with telesales/retail channel.

2) Place a FTTH DTAG/OXG activation order with 150 tariff.

3) Check if obtained Barcode has passed through POS system and reached 1270.

4) Check the SOM logs triggered from POS.

5) Verify that conditionServiceName value is passed incorrectly.

 

*Test Details:*

Order ID: 1254433, 1253549, 1253533

Barcode ID: VDE7730015271, VDE5730015073, VDE7730015071

Env : ACC2/IT

 

*Actual Result:* Incorrect conditionServiceName passed in SOM logs for tariff promo ID P-0370-01-01. 

*Expected Result:* Correct conditionServiceName should be passed in SOM logs for tariff promo ID P-0370-01-01.
column367: FTTH DTAG/OXG activation orders with particular promo E2E flow will get impacted as Barcodes go to error state after BE processing due to this issue.

column1: OSF | Wave 10.1 | ACC2 | IT | All orders are stuck at INITIAL state in IT2ROM DB
column39:
We have observed that all orders are getting stuck at INITIAL state in IT2ROM DB for ACC2/IT env.

*Error:* Caused by: org.springframework.jdbc.BadSqlGrammarException: PreparedStatementCallback; bad SQL grammar []; nested exception is java.sql.SQLSyntaxErrorException: ORA-00904: "EXTERNAL_DOC_POSITION": invalid identifier

 

*Steps to Reproduce:*

1) Login Omnius with telesales/retail channel.

2) Initiate a Mobile/Cable/DSL activation/ILS order.

3) Navigate to CS/CD retrieval page.

4) Check the CS/CD ID status in IT2ROMDB.

5) Verify that all orders are getting stuck at INITIAL state.

 

*Actual Result:* Orders are getting stuck at INITIAL state in IT2ROM DB. 

*Expected Result:* Orders should not get stuck at INITIAL state in IT2ROM DB and successfully get processed without any issue.
column367: Order submission will get impacted due to this issue.
column612:
Development Team suggested some configuration changes and SPN-OPT-000143320 has been raised by IXCF Team with Development Team for this issue. Development team will raise a resubmission for the same for correction purpose.
After making configuration changes, we have restarted IT OM and orders are getting processed successfully.
column918:
07/Oct/25 2:20 PM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;After OCA.000163106(OC.000163074) & OCA.000163119(OC.000163117) deployment, all the orders in IT2ROM DB are stuck in INITIAL state.

TEMS Team is checking with FN TID Team.;;;
column919:
07/Oct/25 4:09 PM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;Updates from TEMS Team:



We have received below update from IXCF Team,

“OM Development Team has confirmed that there was a code error, which is temporarily fixed. *SPN-OPT-000143320* has been raised with Development Team for this error.

Development team will raise a resubmission for the same for correction purpose”.

We are restarting IT OM Application, and we will update once Application is up.;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 10.1 | CR-880 | ACC2 | The values passed for legitimation do not match the required design
column39:
When Agent perform Customer search with customers using other legitimation methods that the values ​​passed for legitimation do not match the required design.

for example, instead of "SOFT_AUTHENTICATION" we send "SOFT", instead of “SERVICE_PIN” we send "SERVICE_PIN_CAB".

 

response body:

{   "value" : "unable to parse or validate session token: Cannot construct instance of `cops.callhandling.api.model.CustomerSessionTokenClaims$LegitimationEnum`, problem: Unexpected value 'SOFT'\n at [Source: UNKNOWN; byte offset: #UNKNOWN] (through reference chain: cops.callhandling.api.model.CustomerSessionTokenClaims[\"legitimation\"])" }

 

response body:

{

  "value" : "unable to parse or validate session token: Cannot construct instance of `cops.callhandling.api.model.CustomerSessionTokenClaims$LegitimationEnum`, problem: Unexpected value 'SERVICE_PIN_CAB'\n at [Source: UNKNOWN; byte offset: #UNKNOWN|#UNKNOWN] (through reference chain: cops.callhandling.api.model.CustomerSessionTokenClaims[\"legitimation\"])"

 

*Steps to reproduce:*

1. Login to Omnius Telesales/Retail channel.
2. Perform the Customer search 
3. Click on Handover to ADT button over the UI

Actual result: Customers using other legitimation methods that the values ​​passed for legitimation do not match the required design.

Expected Result:  

Agent Desktop: SOFT_AUTHENTICATION, NO_LEGITIMATION, MTAN, SERVICE_PIN, ALTERNATIVE, CUSTOMER_PASSWORD
column367: Agent not able perform Customer search using other legitimation methods
column918: 07/Oct/25 12:12 AM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com]  any update?;;;
column919:
08/Oct/25 10:31 AM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Kshitij Kumar Srivastava added a comment - 
Hi [~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com] 
I had a call with VF design team, and their expectation is to have these below possible values in ADT system.

somehow it was missed in our Technical US for #2 and #4,
 # NO_LEGITIMATION,

 # SOFT_AUTHENTICATION,

 # MTAN, 

 # SERVICE_PIN,

 # ALTERNATIVE

 # CUSTOMER_PASSWORD

VF consider this as valid defect. 
means, (SPIN_MOB_AUTHENTICATION and SPIN_CAB_AUTHENTICATION and future SPIN_DSL_AUTHENTICATION) considers as SERVICE_PIN
So OSE team is fixing this defect ;;;

03/Oct/25 5:05 PM;bharath.krishnamurthy@vodafone.com;[~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com] [~pallavi.kokate1@vodafone.com] [~nasir.sayyad@vodafone.com] 

 
Pragathi Prakash
 
added a comment -
 
Hi Natasa,
 
This is expected behaviour of SPIN_CAB → when there is technical skip as per CR760 PART 5 
The error message shown is for the technical skip occured for the cable account when SPIN authentication was not possible for cab account. 
Hence same is applicable in this usecase for CR920


Explanation : 
1. As on CR760 Part5 ,if SPINCAB has technical skip , there will be red banner with the respective message over 2OFX window- (Radio button view) . ( as we have default auth as 2ofx with 2 radio button) 
2. As on CR909 the next default authentication if SPIN_CAB fails ( due to technical skip) is 3X4 ( as we introduced separate authentication & authentication windows for 2OFX & 3X4 in CR909) 
For a linked account ( MOB +CAB ) 
3. Hence for Mob account → SPIN_MOB is eligible for auth & has technical skip - next eligible auth is SPINCAB is offered: Working fine as per description 
and Cab account→ SPINCAB s eligible for auth & has technical skip - next eligible auth for cab account 3X4 is offered : working fine as per description , as well as we see SPINCAB was not possible with red banner message :- Working as expected from combined outcomes of CR760 PART 5 ( ref 1. ) , CR909 (ref 2.)
Hence we see red banner reason for why spin_cab authentication was not possible & next auth 3X4 is offered to continue. 
Evidence of valid output in production code 

We also request vfde_dxl_spin_mobile_service- & vfde_dxl_spin_service logs in order to verify the exact response obtained for each account.;;;

column919:
29/Sep/25 1:55 PM;yogesh.borade1@vodafone.com;9/29/2025 10:41 AM
We checked the COM logs and identified an error. Upon checking the CCB logs, we found that a response is present. However, the barcode is still in the 1296 WAIT_SLS state.
 
COM LOG:
2025.09.27 14:40:08,674 [mcf-default-listener-3]  WARN 001949708413 Order-VDE7730014490 orderPosition-1 does not contain 'processingStatus' or 'completionStatusNewCcbId' parameters, assuming 'not known to CCM'
 
CCB LOG:
{"number":"334 ","message":"INFO  | [RequestHandler-6] | Setting status of FifTransaction VDE7730014490-1-1758976810792-413692328 to RESPONSE_SENT","environment":"IT","log":"2025-09-27T12:40:45.334162083Z stdout F 2025-09-27 14:40:45,334 | INFO  | [RequestHandler-6] | Setting status of FifTransaction VDE7730014490-1-1758976810792-413692328 to RESPONSE_SENT","pod":"fif-comsomqueueclient-deployment-5fc4f495c5-wjtnv","apptime":"2025-09-27 14:40:45"}
 
currently Marco is checking on it;;;
column920:
30/Sep/25 1:43 PM;yogesh.borade1@vodafone.com;30/09/2025 01:32 PM We have checked and found below errors in COM,
 
2025.09.29 11:19:50,346 [fifThreadGroup-3] ERROR VDE7730014538 No enum constant net.arcor.orderschema.ProcessingType.
de.arcor.com.utils.exception.ComException: No enum constant net.arcor.orderschema.ProcessingType.
        at de.arcor.com.orderProcessor.actions.impl.AbstractAction.baseExecute(AbstractAction.java:155)
 
In Java, might be enums are a special type that define a fixed set of constants. When you use Enum.valueOf(String name), the string must exactly match one of the enum constant names. If it doesn’t, Java throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: No enum constant <EnumClass>.<value> error.
 
As discussed, it appears that no enum value is being entered during the SWLAN addition process from the OSF front end.
 
We have highlighted this issue to the DEV team.;;;

column924:
03/Oct/25 11:35 AM;affan.baragazi@vodafone.com;Hi [~sneha.wayal1@vodafone.com] ,

While performing legacySearch, OGW prepares the header params as follows:
1. bpId --> 'OGW' + currentTimeStamp

2. bpName --> 'OGW_BKSService:SearchCustomerBANSubscriber'

3. boId --> same as bpId

It then prepares the searchCustomerBanRequest and calls the service first with MarketCode as "MMC" followed by another call updating the marketCode to "MMO".
This implementation has been in place for quite some time. Please let me know if any further discussion is needed. Thanks;;;
column925:
03/Oct/25 12:40 PM;sneha.wayal1@vodafone.com;Hi Affan,

Can you please go through latest email from Andreas.

[^AW OSF OGW use of SearchCustBANSub001-SearchCustomerBANSubscriber (II).msg]

Hi Sneha,

 

the reply is not correct in almost all topics as highlighted in already attached email in yellow the bpName is sent  <bas:bpName>CustomerAccount002:SearchCustomerBANSubscriber as seen in Tibco logs. BKS would be something for FixedNet but this is Mobile for Kias so 2. Is wrong and bpName has to be corrected for SoapAction used.

 

Concerning 1. OGW1758878870199 Tibco does not care how OSF is generating their bpId but the 2 separate invocations of the service first for MMC then for MMO each have to have a unique bpId, that is a operational requirement as shared to all developing parties using Tibco EAI/ESB. If the timestamp only has definition of seconds then this is not sufficient to being unique, but this has to be ensure by each client. OGW has to correct this !

 

If OSF/OGW is using boId same as bpId then they did not understand the purpose of those 2 parameters and have to read the specifications.

 

Finally doing same request for both marketCodes MMC and MMO does not make sense, any customer can only belong to one market. This violates the principal of avoiding unnecessary load on backends Tibco EAI and Kias. If OGW does not know the market of customer/BAN according to spec the parameter can be sent as empty and Tibco will check by eaiGtMarket first.
|Backend Interface|KIAS|If marketCode field is empty in request, then the following Service will be invoked|
|Protocol|Tuxedo|
|Operation|eaiGtMarket|
|Service|CSM145|
|CSM service to SearchCustomerBANSubscriber|
|Protocol|Tuxedo|
|Operation|eaiSrchCstBan|
|Service|CSM144|

So this should be changed as well.

 

Pls add this full mail to ticket.

Kind regards, Andreas;;;

09/Oct/25 5:45 PM;atharva.paskanthi@vodafone.com;*OSF | Wave10.1 | Checkpoint | DM | OS-77932 | ACC2 | MoM and Action items (9th October, 2025)*


1) The reply is not correct in almost all topics as highlighted in already attached email in yellow the bpName is sent  <bas:bpName>CustomerAccount002:SearchCustomerBANSubscriber as seen in Tibco logs. BKS would be something for FixedNet but this is Mobile for Kias so 2. Is wrong and bpName has to be corrected for SoapAction used.

2) Concerning 1. OGW1758878870199 Tibco does not care how OSF is generating their bpId but the 2 separate invocations of the service first for MMC then for MMO each have to have a unique bpId, that is a operational requirement as shared to all developing parties using Tibco EAI/ESB. If the timestamp only has definition of seconds then this is not sufficient to being unique, but this has to be ensure by each client. OGW has to correct this !

If OSF/OGW is using boId same as bpId then they did not understand the purpose of those 2 parameters and have to read the specifications.

3) Finally doing same request for both marketCodes MMC and MMO does not make sense, any customer can only belong to one market. This violates the principal of avoiding unnecessary load on backends Tibco EAI and Kias. If OGW does not know the market of customer/BAN according to spec the parameter can be sent as empty and Tibco will check by eaiGtMarket first.


- The above 3 points were discussed with Andreas Knocke , Ketaki and Snehal
- As discussed nothing was changed and this is the behavior in Production env as well
- [~sneha.wayal1@vodafone.com] will update the ticket title and description and reduce priority to P3
- As Ketaki mentioned first 2 points will be fixed by this ticket in the upcoming deliveries.
- For the 3rd point we need to raise a separate P3 ticket as it is a Design Gap and need to be fixed via Change request;;;

column1: OSF | Wave10.1 | ACC2 | Customer DOB in the Legitimation section is not prefilled from the Save Cart section for Mobile Prepaid Retail New ACQ
column39:
We are getting error Date of Birth field not being pre-selected and showing an error in the Legitimation details section during the save and send shopping cart flow for mobile prepaid.

 

*Steps to Reproduce:*

 
1.Log in Omnius as a Retail Agent and select shop.
2.Selct Private as a Customer type.
3.Select Mobile prepaid package.
4.Add Blister and Tariff.
5.Click on speichern & senden button for saving cart and add mandatory details (Name,Sirname,Birth date).
7.Again add details and Retrive saved cart
8.Verify all the product details along with price are correctly displayed in shopping and extended shopping cart. 
9.Click on Zum chekout button.
10. 1. Fill all details on checkout like customer name, address.
       - Select foreign (non-German) nationality.
       2. Add Legitimation details and verify all details.
       - Select Foreign ID card (ausl. Personalausweis) as Type of ID card.
 
*Actual Result:* Date of Birth field not being pre-selected and showing an error in the Legitimation details section during the save and send shopping cart flow for mobile prepaid
 
*Expected Result:* Date of Birth field should be pre-selected in the Legitimation details section during the save and send shopping cart flow for mobile prepaid
column367: Agent cannot submit Mobile prepaid order in case of save and shopping cart.
column612: As it is prefilled based on the DOB in kunden data section,it is not stored as a checkout parameter under legitimation section, hence when you reload the saved cart we might not get this DOB in legitimation section populated .
column918:
23/Sep/25 12:33 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Shruti Kanchan added a comment -
 
Yes, “save cart” was not in the scope of OS-971. If this is required, it must be addressed with VF BA as part of the CR;;;
column919:

column922:
19/Sep/25 3:16 PM;yogesh.borade1@vodafone.com;Please update below comments in the same defect:
 
We have received below inputs from POSFE Team addressing the issue:
It seems there had been some client related problems to reach it. In these cases always try to restart the session – maybe it will solve the problem.
 
If some order does not reach COM, please check the order in POS-FE and check for its state.
 
Has it been imported?   (Have other orders been imported?)
If  only some orders have not been imported – it could be because the barcode had been used once before.
Reason why it is not visible  could be also: cpcom agent + Import Auftrag agent have not run, the corresponding POSDB / EFFONL database had not been available during at run time.
Is there any clearing required?  If yes -  the order cannot be sent to other systems -> you need to solve that problems first.
As there are several agents running in the database – one execution of an agent,  consuming a long processing time  will lead to delay of execution of others.
Sometimes a lost Oracle connection could also prevent some agent to finish in time or get it stuck – then a restart of the system might be necessary.
 
For the given barcodes  they have been imported by need clearing – the chosen tariff seems to be expired! (not allowed for customer contracts signed after 15.9.2025)

  !image-2025-09-19-15-15-00-731.png|width=657,height=347!
  !image-2025-09-19-15-15-31-695.png|width=665,height=399!
 
  !image-2025-09-19-15-16-01-201.png|width=724,height=46!
In this case –  POSFE Team had set the config for that part to be terminated like it would had been done in Oct.

  !image-2025-09-19-15-16-16-674.png|width=651,height=395!
Kindly perform actions based on stated remarks and retest accordingly.;;;

column921:
22/Sep/25 12:50 PM;alka.kshirsagar2@vodafone.com;Comment from Ursula: 

SignoSign has not changed and to say it in short words: this is no feasible workaround for production and OM must be fixed before your launch.

 

The reason is that the document identification must always be in white colour in size >0 pt in footer of first page, it must never be visible or made visible, shop representative can even not click in adobe reader and especially not for every such contract summary.

 

SignoSign was working fine with the 'white on white' identification in footer before. Since OM has changed and it's not working anymore, OM must be corrected to solve the issue.    

 

Best regards 

Ursula ;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 10.1 | ACC2 | 3X4 authentication window is not displayed upon skipping SPIN_MOB technically and SPIN_CAB with inactive Cable PIN
column39:
We have observed that 3X4 authentication window is not displayed upon skipping SPIN_MOB technically and SPIN_CAB with inactive Cable PIN in ACC2 env.

 

*Steps to Reproduce:*

1) Make sure relevant permissions are assigned to Back-Office agent as below.

SOFT_AUTHENTICATION -> Disable

FLEXIBLE_AUTHENTICATION -> Enable

2OFX_AUTHENTICATION -> Enable

3X4_AUTHENTICATION -> Enable

SPIN_MOB_ AUTHENTICATION -> Enable

SPIN_CAB_ AUTHENTICATION -> Enable

MTAN_AUTHENTICATION -> Disable

2) Login to Omnius Telesales channel with Back-Office agent.

3) Search an existing linked (MOB+CAB) private customer where Mobile customer has active PIN and cable customer has inactive PIN.

4) 360 view page will be loaded.

5) Click on the customer authentication button.

6) SPIN_MOB authentication window will be displayed.

7) Skip SPIN_MOB authentication technically by providing incorrect PIN twice.

8) SPIN_CAB authentication window will be slipped automatically due to inactive PIN.

9) Validate that 3X4 authentication window is not displayed.

 

*Customer ID:* 
LK_21417----
MOB Customer: 120599784 -> PIN: 560861
CAB Customer: 935364938 -> PIN: 813184
 

*Actual Result:* 3X4 authentication window is not displayed upon skipping SPIN_MOB technically and SPIN_CAB with inactive Cable PIN.

*Expected Result:* 3X4 authentication window should be displayed upon skipping SPIN_MOB technically and SPIN_CAB with inactive Cable PIN.
column367: Agent is unable to authenticate linked (MOB+CAB) private customer where Mobile customer has active PIN and cable customer has inactive PIN using 3X4 authentication window as it is not displayed/offered in Omnius.
column612:
RCA : As part of skipping from SpinMob due to failed authentication, SpinCable getStatus service call failed due to any reason, and the fallback to next authentication was not happening as its missed to handle that scenario in code 
We have delivered a full  build delivery  towards ACC2  for W10.1

column1: OSF | Wave 10.1 | ACC2 | IT | DSL/FTTH retail activation orders are stuck at 1469(SEND_POS) state in COM DB
column39:
We have observed that DSL/FTTH retail activation orders are stuck at 1469(SEND_POS) state in COM DB in ACC2/IT env.

*Note:* CPCOM Import agent is not running at regular intervals.

 

*Steps to Reproduce:*

1) Login to Omnius retail channel.

2) Place a DSL activation order from Omnius.

2) Check the Obtained Barcode in COM.

3) Verify that Barcode is stuck at 1469(SEND_POS) state in COM DB.

 

*Test Details:*

Order ID: 1243129, 1242993, 1243105

Barcode ID: VDE7730013100, VDE7730013080, VDE7730013097 

Env : ACC2/IT

 

*Actual Result:* Orders are getting stuck at 1469(SEND_POS) state in COM DB. 

*Expected Result:* Orders should successfully reach Backend system without any issue.
column367: DSL retail activation orders cannot be processed E2E due to this issue.
column612: No update received from POSFE Team, but CPCOM Import agent started running again in IT POSFE and orders started progressing ahead of 1469 in IT COMDB.

column1: OSF | Wave 10.1 | ACC2 | IT | DSL ILS orders are stuck at 1235(ALLOCATE_CCB_ID) state in COM DB
column39:
We have observed that DSL ILS orders are stuck at 1235(ALLOCATE_CCB_ID) state in COM DB in ACC2/IT env.

 

*Steps to Reproduce:*

1) Place a DSL ILS order from Omnius.

2) Check the Obtained Barcode in COM.

3) Verify that Barcode is stuck at 1235(ALLOCATE_CCB_ID) state in COM DB.

 

*Test Details:*

Order ID: 1242913, 1242989, 1243113

Barcode ID: VDE7730013063, VDE7730013078, VDE7730013099

Env : ACC2/IT

 

*Actual Result:* Orders are getting stuck at 1235(ALLOCATE_CCB_ID) state in COM DB. 

*Expected Result:* Orders should successfully reach Backend system without any issue.
column367: DSL ILS orders cannot be processed E2E due to this issue.
column612:
Dev team confirmed that exception was not the issue and order was successfully confirmed from FIF side.

There might be bit delay in reflecting over DB.
column919:
17/Sep/25 1:23 PM;yogesh.borade1@vodafone.com;Resolution Date & Time: 9/17/2025 11:57 AM



Dev team confirmed that exception was not the issue and order was successfully confirmed from FIF side.

There might be bit delay in reflecting over DB.

Issue is resolved, order reached to backend.;;;

column1: OSF | Wave10.1 | ACC2 | IT | DSL-GetMarketingPermissions service failing with EAI002605 error code
column39:
We have observed that DSL-GetMarketingPermissions service failing with EAI002605 error code in ACC2/IT env.

 

*Error description:*

<ErrorDescription>An error was encountered while invoking WS.Details [Error_Code: EAI002605 , Error_Message: HttpCommunicationException , Error_Type: Infrastructure , Error_Severity: E , Error_Information: BW-HTTP-100300:An IOException was thrown while trying to execute the Http method;]</ErrorDescription>

 

*Steps to Reproduce:*

1) Login to Omnius telesales/retail channel.

2) Peform customer search using existing DSL/FTTH customer.

3) Verify that error banner is displayed in omnius.

 

*Test Data:*

Customer ID: 001936051814, 001942507205

Env : ACC2/IT

 

*Actual Result:* DSL customer search not working as GetMarketingPermissions service failing with EAI002605 error code. 

*Expected Result:* DSL customer search should work fine without any issue.
column367: Customer Marketing Information (BEW Permission) will not be retrieved in Omnius FE.
column612:
issue had resolved last week with KIAS reboot of KIAS pack
We have removed the expired intermediate cert to Archive and restarted CUS-ESB module to fix the issue.

column1: OSF | Wave10.1 | ACC2 | Account holder option is getting changed when Agent clicks on weiter button without entering IBAN in payment section for Mobile SOHO Business New ACQ.
column39:
We have observed, Account holder option is getting changed from Kunde ist Kontoinhaber (Customer is account holder) to Abweichender Kontoinhaber (Different account holder) when Agent clicks on Weiter button without entering IBAN in payment section for Mobile SOHO Business New ACQ.

Please find below screenshots:

!image-2025-09-16-16-27-53-293.png|width=401,height=646!

!image-2025-09-16-16-28-34-274.png|width=399,height=502!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Telesales channel.
 # Create Mobile SOHO Business package in shopping cart.
 # Proceed to checkout.
 # Enter mandatory customer details and proceed.
 # Clicks on Weiter button without entering IBAN in payment section.
 # Observed Account holder option is getting changed from Kunde ist Kontoinhaber (Customer is account holder) to Abweichender Kontoinhaber (Different account holder)

Actual: Account holder option is getting changed from Kunde ist Kontoinhaber (Customer is account holder) to Abweichender Kontoinhaber (Different account holder) when Agent clicks on weiter button without entering IBAN in payment section for Mobile SOHO Business New ACQ.

Expected: Account holder option should not change automatically.

Reference story: [OS-9067] Omnius CHCK As an agent, I want to be able to capture company name as bank account owner related to Mobile SOHO Business customer, so that correct account owner is provided [OS-9067] - Vodafone Global Jira
column367: Agent needs to manually change the Account holder type back to the original option.
column612:
RCA: Issue is due to the old implementation logic where its having only one option called Alternate account holder, now with latest we have one more option called same as customer account and both share same data-id which is causing the above issue. Its corrected by using specific element id instead on data-id.
We have delivered a full build delivery  towards ACC2  for W10.1

Details will be available on https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OSFCICD-944

Please refer below table for all the details related to deliverables.




KIAS2000_CN_19435

OSE : 11.0.0-B116

Sandbox: 11.0.0-B116

column39:

Notification Message: Die Mobile Portierung ist nur für Online-Ident und SOHO Ident möglich

Please find below screenshots:

 # Login to Omnius as Telesales channel.
 # Create Mobile Postpaid package.

 # Select other than Online or SOHO ident in identification section.
 # Omnius shows Porting notification message.
 # Clicks on Weiter button and error message automatically removed.
 # Proceed next and clicks on generate contract button.
 # Once contract summary generates clicks on Zurück zum Checkout button.

Actual: Porting notification message is not removed from the checkout page when the agent returns to the checkout page using the 'Back to checkout' button.

Expected: Porting Notification Message should be automatically removed from checkout after agent clicks on Weiter button in Customer Data page.

column1: SPN-DK-000143258 ITQATESTRP-147586 | OSF | ACC2 | Wave 10.1 | PR | DSL Retail | DMS Processing | Unable to process fixednet files in DMS due to prokey issue
column39:
We are getting the below error in Prokey window while processing Fixednet DMS Pares files in PR DMS Server, after launching {*}modulestart_all.cmd{*}.

Error:

!image-2025-09-15-20-07-17-756.png|width=380,height=250!

 

Scenario Name: DSL Retail new activation 

*Steps to Re-produce:*
1. Login to Omnius via retail channel.
2. Check Serviceability.
3. Add DSL package.
4. Proceed to checkout.
5. Fill in required details.
6. Generate contract documents.
7. Submit the order and send it for pares processing.
8. Send WebDms and Fixednet Files for OneDMS and DMS processing.

 

*Actual Result:*

Unable to process fixednet files in DMS due to prokey issue

*Expected Result:*
Fixednet files should processed in PR DMS successfully.

Test data: 

Server: dea519yw.eito-dublin.local prod IP / 139.47.225.155 - Worker server

File used for processing -

column1: OSF | Wave10.1 | ACC2 | CS is being created window appears even after receiving error message from backend in Telesales channel.

column1: OSF API | Wave 10.1 | ACC2 | INT | Script Assertion failure received
column39:
*ENV:* ACC2

*Issue :* In OSF API testing, we are performing scenarios using ReadyAPI, while performing the flow we have observed that some of scenarios are failing with Script Assertion failure.

 

*Steps to reproduce:*
 # Launch the ReadyAPI
 # Goto > Functional Test 
 # Run Requests 
 # validate All responses

*Expected:* Request should be executed without any error.

*Actual:* Request is failed due to Script Assertion Error

column929:
24/Sep/25 6:10 PM;gaurav.lanjewar1@vodafone.com;Hi All, As discussed on the call,
 * For bundles, a separate PCAT is maintained :Philipp.
 * Vishal recreated the flow.
 * A predefined script is used to check product compatibility & Errors occur only if changes are made: Vishal Raut, Vodafone
 * Whenever there’s a change in PCAT, the assertion result must be updated : Sunil Kumar C M1.
 * No changes are made on OSE without a formal Change Request (CR).: Sunil Kumar C M1
 * Sunil Kumar C M1 needs to check with Waseem and reschedule a call.;;;
column930:
25/Sep/25 5:45 PM;gaurav.lanjewar1@vodafone.com;Hi All, As discussed on today's call ,
 * Gigakombi Liberations implemented a new PCAT bundle to ACC2 : ⁠Philipp Röper, Vodafone (External)
 * ⁠Waseem Akhtar, Vodafone (External), : the APIs depend on rules to function. If these rules are removed, the APIs will not work.
 * ⁠Waseem Akhtar, Vodafone (External) ⁠Pramodkumar Chauhan, Vodafone compared the bundle files and found that data has been significantly reduced in ACC2, which is causing the issues.
 * To restore functionality, rules need to be added back into the import XML file.
 * The catalog is delivered by PAPS : ⁠Waseem Akhtar, Vodafone (External)
 * ⁠Waseem Akhtar, Vodafone (External) suggests that reverting the PCAT changes is the only viable solution.
 * ⁠Philipp Röper, Vodafone (External) will revert the changes till end of next week - 3rd October, and the team will check with TID afterward.;;;

column1: OSF | Wave10.1 | ACC2 | Hardware non availability error message is not removed even after selecting another delivery option.
column39:
We have observed, Hardware non availability error message not removed even after selecting another delivery option.

Please find below screenshots:

!image-2025-09-15-17-11-53-936.png|width=549,height=288!

!image-2025-09-15-17-12-24-357.png|width=375,height=425!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Retail channel.
 # Create Mobile with Cable package in shopping cart.
 # Proceed to checkout.
 # Select Direct Delivery option for Mobile.
 # Omnius shows error message window for unavailability of Direct delivery option for selected hardware (Keine Direktherausgabe wegen Nicht-Verfügbarkeit möglich. Bitte wähle eine andere Lieferoption.).
 # Select another delivery option.
 # Observed still error message not removed.

Actual: Hardware non availability error message not removed even after selecting another delivery option.

Expected: Hardware non availability error message should be removed after selecting another delivery option.

Reference ticket: OS-28835 OSF | ACC2 | Wave 7.2 | Hardware non availability error message not removed even after selecting another delivery option. - Vodafone Global Jira

Hi Satish/Ajay ,

Based on further analysis we can see the package created is Postpaid and the product selected is Sim-Only Tariff. In this case the package does not contain any product which belongs to *NoIdent → catagory.* If at least one product on package belongs to *NoIdent* category we will send NoIdentFlag as Y else N.

IF *ALL the mobile postpaid ACQ / MIGCOC package(s) contain at least one products of the category "NoIdent"* (OS-961), then the system sets the boolean NoIdentFlag to 'Y', else to 'N'

15/Sep/25 4:20 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Shifali Guleria added a comment -
 
Hi [~sura.radha1@vodafone.com] [~nasir.sayyad@vodafone.com] 

CR907 scope is for Private customer
The mentioned customer is SOHO so according to existing logic the ILS button will be disabled
So this is not a valid defect

*Existing situation:*

*ILS button*
IF DunningStatus = IN_DUNNING
THEN ILS button is disabled
ELSE ILS button is enabled

*VVL check button (banner with button) i.e. section "VVL prüfen".*
IF (DunningStatus = IN_DUNNING OR CustomerStatus = D) AND current contract > 18 month
THEN VVL is allowed
ELSEIF (DunningStatus = IN_DUNNING OR CustomerStatus = D) AND current contract < 18 month
THEN VVLcheck (banner+button) is hidden
ELSE 
VVL is allowed
h3. As per CR907

*ILS button and VVL check button*

IF (DunningStatus = IN_DUNNING OR CollectionDelinquentStatus = D) AND CustomerStatus = S/N
THEN ILS button disabled AND VVL check (banner+button) not show
ELSE ILS button enabled AND VVL check (banner+button) is shown

column1: OSF | Wave 10.1 | ACC2 | Red banner message is always displayed after a GigaKombi eligiblity check
column39:
While performing Gigacombi scenario for MOB+CAB to check Red Banner message in Frontend in case of Technical serivecs down , we are getting below error message
{*}ERROR-{*}Ein technischer Fehler ist aufgetreten. Bitte versuche es später erneut.(Correlation-ID: fscugmv2c1hiqkpm37go7l0lpd)
Issue is related to a JWT token error -> [OS-58148] OMNIUS_OSE_As Omnius, I want to call the DXL(oauth) API to get the JWT token so that it can be used to initiate the request for DXL(eligibility) Interface (OS-58148) - Vodafone Global Jira

+*Steps to Reproduce:*+

1.Login toTelesales channel
2.select mobile package
3.select cable package

4.click on weiter button

5.Modal window should be visible

6. fill all mandatory details

7.click on prufen button

8.Red banner should be visible with Correct error message

 

+*Actual Result:*+
We recieve "-ERROR-Ein technischer Fehler ist aufgetreten. Bitte versuche es später erneut.(Correlation-ID: fscugmv2c1hiqkpm37go7l0lpd)" error message after any type of GigaKombi eligibility check". According to logs we recieve error code 403

{color:#00875a}{"faultstring": Access to resource /oauth2/token is forbidden.} {color}
{color:#00875a}status: functional {color}
{color:#00875a}status reason: functional error{color}

 

+*Expected Result:*+
Eligibility service response should be matching the customer type and product configuration aswell as considering matching logic for building a GigaKombi and therefor display green/yellow/red banner accordingly.

column1: OSF | Wave 10.0, 10.1, 10.0.2 | ACC | Address with empty house number addition is being filled with asterisk (*) mark automatically during Serviceability

column927:
16/Sep/25 5:22 PM;natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com;On VFP side nothing was changed!

This issue seems to be related to the PST bug: [[PSTBUG-3509] PAPI | OSF | VKD,VFW | All orders are failing with Delivery & Billing address error message - DE Jira|https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/PSTBUG-3509]

Answer from developer:

Hello,
The issue is in IBP (IRIS) when it contacts AdsFacade to validate the sent addresses. The exact field causing the issue is houseNumberAddition. When the field is omitted in the request, AdsFacade returns an asterisk in the candidate addresses. When the address is compared with the candidate address returned from AdsFacade, the validation fails (becasue null != '*'). 
A workaround can be applied in IRIS to ignore asterisks in both the address and the candidate address when comparing them as it's already a wildcard.

[~anna-mariya.robeto@vodafone.com] could you please update us as soon as the PST bug is solved. The PST bug was created only fr test1b, but we have this issue on all ACC environments. Thank you;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 10.1 | ACC2 | ProductOffering request body is missing meta node/parameter
column39:
It was observed that we recieve a "HTTP_ERROR.500.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR" for GigaKombi eligibility call. Reason for that is that the "meta" node/parameter is missing in the request body. Because of that, CDH service validation returns code 503 which is then returned as code 500 by DXL.

 

+*Pre-condition:*+
 - Agent without permission "BLOCK_GKL"

+*Steps to reproduce:*+

1. Configure shopping cart

2. Initiate GKL eligibility check

+*Actual result:*+

GK eligibility service is returning a "500" error. "meta" node/parameter is missing in the productOffering body data

+request body details:+

{color:#172b4d}_{_{color}

{color:#172b4d}     _"channel": {_{color}

{color:#172b4d}          _"id":"OSF",_{color}

{color:#172b4d}          _"name":"One Sales Foundation"_{color}

{color:#172b4d}      _}_{color}

 

+*Expected result:*+

GK eligibility service should return information based on the GK eligibility for the customer. "meta" node/parameter is included in the productOffering body data

+Expected request body content:+

_{_

    _{color:#00875a}*"meta": {*{color}_

        _"channel": {_

            _"id": "OSF",_

            _"name": "One Sales Foundation"_

        _}_

    _{color:#00875a}*}*{color},_

 

+*Additional info:*+
 - Check screenshot for "PostProductOfferingGigakombiElgibilityBodyData" request spec

column1: OSF | Wave10.1 | ACC2 | Agent can change customer type from SOHO B to SOHO BRV if agent returns to shopping cart from checkout page in Retail channel.
column39:
We have observed, Agent can change the customer type from SOHO B to SOHO BRV if the agent returns to the shopping cart from the checkout page in the Retail channel.

Please find below screenshots:

!image-2025-09-09-22-19-45-344.png|width=526,height=263!

Agent returns to the shopping cart from the checkout page:

!image-2025-09-09-22-33-45-398.png|width=522,height=274!

!image-2025-09-09-22-34-12-843.png|width=521,height=273!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Retail channel.
 # Search existing Mobile customer.
 # Clicks on modify package.
 # Change tariff in shopping cart.
 # Proceed to checkout.
 # Return back to shopping cart.
 # Check customer type.
 # Agent is able to change customer type.

Actual: Agent can change the customer type from SOHO B to SOHO BRV if the agent returns to the shopping cart from the checkout page in the Retail channel.

Expected: Agent should not be able to change customer type and Firma mit Privatkundentarif should be shown in customer segment.
column367: Agent can change customer type for existing customer which will lead order failure during order fulfillment.

column1: OSF | Wave10.1 | ACC2 | Semicolon missing in Monthly payment section after IBAN text in Voicelog page.
column39:
While performing Mobile Postpaid New Activation scenario, We have observed, Semicolon missing in Monthly payment section after IBAN text in Voicelog page.

Please find below screenshot:

!image-2025-09-06-16-52-25-418.png|width=389,height=286!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Telesales channel.
 # Create Mobile Postpaid valid package in shopping cart.
 # Proceed to checkout.
 # Enter IBAN in Payment section.
 # Verify Monthly payment section in Voicelog page.

Actual: Semicolon missing in Monthly payment section after IBAN text in Voicelog page.

Expected: Semicolon should be printed in Monthly payment section after IBAN text in Voicelog page.

Reference screenshot from Voicelog design document:

!image-2025-09-06-16-54-11-911.png|width=463,height=243!
column367: Display Issue - No Impact on functional flow.
column612:
During masking the the semicolon was replaced with masked data, due to that semicolon was missed from there.

column1: OSF | Wave10.1 | ACC2 | Shopping cart is not being deleted after clicking the 'Delete All Packages' button.
column39:
We have observed, Shopping cart is not being deleted after clicking the 'Delete All Packages' button.

Error Message is shown in console:

customerDe.js:1072 Uncaught ReferenceError: *AGENT_HAS_ALLOW_MOB is not defined*
    at window.CustomerDe.updatePackagesByBusinessType (customerDe.js:1072:20)
    at window.CustomerDe.handleCustomerType (customerDe.js:166:18)
    at HTMLButtonElement.<anonymous> (init.js:724:20)
    at HTMLDivElement.dispatch (jquery-3.4.1.min.js:2:42571)
    at v.handle (jquery-3.4.1.min.js:2:40572)
    at HTMLDivElement.wrappingFn (event-target-patch.js:79:1)

Please find below screenshots:

!image-2025-09-06-16-33-12-624.png|width=523,height=275!

!image-2025-09-06-16-33-36-365.png|width=522,height=274!

!image-2025-09-06-16-28-25-351.png|width=522,height=274!

!image-2025-09-06-16-28-59-220.png|width=524,height=275!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Telesales channel.
 # Create Mobile Postpaid Package in shopping cart with Hardware and Tariff.
 # Clicks on Alle pakete Loschen button.
 # Warning message shown and Agent accept that.
 # Omnius shows Delete shopping cart Completed but nothing is happening.

Actual: Shopping cart is not being deleted after clicking the 'Delete All Packages' button.

Expected: Shopping cart should be deleted after clicking the 'Delete All Packages' button.

column39:

column920:
10/Sep/25 5:19 PM;gagan.patkar@vodafone.com;Troubleshooting was conducted by logging off all call and response services. Below are the key findings:
 # Performance Issue

 ** The average response time for loading the Order Manager page remains above 40 seconds.
 # High Volume of Orders

 ** More than 1.3 lakh orders are being loaded when accessing the Order Manager page in the ACC2 environment.
 # Role-Based Order Load Variance

 ** The number of loaded orders varies by agent role.
 ** For Back Office agents, the count exceeds 1.3 lakh orders.
 # Environment & Role Specificity

 ** The issue appears to be specific to the ACC2 environment and certain agent roles.
 ** It could not be reproduced in the LNP environment or with the Winback Agent role in ACC2.
 # Next Steps

 ** TechM (Bharat) will conduct an internal discussion and investigate potential solutions at the code or logic level.;;;

03/Oct/25 1:23 PM;gagan.patkar@vodafone.com;Hi [~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com] , [~bharath.krishnamurthy@vodafone.com] ,



I’ve connected with Ajay from the Functional Testing team and confirmed that we’re all using the same agent role: {*}Back Office Agent{*}.

From the {*}ACC2 last release (W9.2){*}, we observed that the *Open Manager page load time for orders* has increased significantly. Previously, it averaged {*}16 to 8 seconds{*}, but it’s now taking {*}over 40 seconds{*}.

The *TID team* has confirmed that the *cron job for order cleanup* is running daily and is removing orders older than {*}90 days{*}.

Additionally, I spoke with *Yogesh from the TEMS team* and tested the {{"NO_PRELOAD_ORDERS"}} permission for the Back Office Agent. We confirmed that enabling this option prevents any records from loading. However, as per {*}Bharat’s input{*}, it should ideally load {*}30 records{*}. Therefore, this option {*}should not be considered a valid mitigation or solution{*}.

Please find the attached snapshot for reference.

06/Oct/25 4:49 PM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;Hi [~bharath.krishnamurthy@vodafone.com] As per the [OS-2204] Omnius_As IT-operations, i want enhance an existing CLI script and introduce a new CLI script for cleaning up orders within a timeframe and certain status, so orders user can see are compliant to legal rules - Vodafone Global Jira
Overview/Description

Due to legal reasons, Omnius is only allowed to display orders for 90 days after they reached status 'completed' in the order manager. After this time span, they should not be shown anymore. Also, we should be able to delete orders with a certain status after a certain submission date. 

Seems CLI script is not working as expected as I can see older than 90 days orders are visible in Order Manager.
Here in below screenshot you can see Order is successful in April month and Order age is 159 days, Could you please check.

column934:
09/Oct/25 10:04 AM;bharath.krishnamurthy@vodafone.com;[~siddhi.varape@vodafone.com] [~gagan.patkar@vodafone.com] 

 
Hari Shankar Malviya
 
added a comment -
 
Hi Siddhi/Gagan,
 
This script is designed to delete records only for the following statuses. All other statuses will remain unaffected.
The deletion is governed by back-office settings, which currently permit the removal of records older than 90 days for the statuses listed below:

OrderCompletedSuccessfully
OrderCompletedWithCancellation
OrderCompletedWithFailure
OrderInProgressWithFailure

Please let me know if you need any further clarification.

Hari;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 10.1 | ACC2 | Email field is missing for Cable SOHO private/SOHO RV private customers during 3X4 authentication when searched customer using legacy search
column39:
We have observed that Email field is missing for Cable SOHO/SOHO RV customers during 3X4 authentication when searched customer using legacy search in ACC2 env.

 

*Steps to Reproduce:*

1) Make sure relevant permissions are assigned to Back-Office agent.

2) Login to Omnius Telesales channel with Back-Office agent.

3) Search a Cable SOHO private or SOHO RV private customer using legacy search.

4) Click on the retrieved customer.

5) 3X4 authentication window will be displayed.

6) Validate only 4 fields are displayed with Email field missing.

 

*Customer ID:* 
CABLE SOHO - 935364065, 935253550
CABLE SOHO RV - 935364064

 

*Actual Result:* Email field is missing for Cable SOHO private/SOHO RV private customers during 3X4 authentication when searched customer using legacy search.

*Expected Result:* Email field should be visible for Cable SOHO private/SOHO RV private customers during 3X4 authentication irrespective of the search type.
column367: Agent is unable to authenticate Cable SOHO private/SOHO RV private customers using Email field during 3X4 authentication as it is missing when searched customer using legacy search.
column612:
RCA: During legacy search or the normal search for soho customers if we don't receive customer sub type is missing in search response then the handling to use default value for customer sub type is missing which is now added. It was only handled on customer 360 for different use case so it is working on customer 360 default.

|OS-971 - blister is mandatory for Prepaid Retail|Service| | |agent.hasOseChannel('Fachhandel,Filiale,Partneragentur')|Product Selection|Mobile->Prepaid_Blister_Retail|Eql(1)|5|manual|ACQ|*|SERVICE-CATEGORY|blister is mandatory for Prepaid Retail|##########| |Prepaid| | | |

is not working as expected. For more details see OS-76802. 

Basically, the rule with operation ‘EQL(1)’ should ensure that when moving to the extended shopping cart in an ACQ Prepaid package, exactly one product from {_}‘{_}{_}Mobile->Prepaid_Blister_Retail’{_} should be in the package if the agent belongs to a certain OSE channel.

We also tried it in a slightly different approach using a restriction to the channel "Retail" - with same effect:
|rule_title|source_type|source_collection|source|service_source_expression|target_type|target|service_target_expression|operation|priority|rule_origin|process_context|channel|operation_type|rule_description|effective_date|expiration_date|package_type_id|override_initial_selectable|ask_confirmation_first|confirmation_text|
|OS-971 - blister is mandatory for Prepaid Retail|Service| | |true|Product Selection|Mobile->Prepaid_Blister_Retail| |Eql(1)|9|import|ACQ|Retail|SERVICE-CATEGORY|blister is mandatory for Prepaid Retail|03.04.2025 00:00| |Prepaid| | | |

This rule does functionally something else than a ‘not allowed’ rule which simply make sure certain products are not shown in the configurator.

As the rule does functionality something else than described before, then this behavior  seems to be a defect and needs to be fixed. It is an essential rule for "Prepaid in Retail" in wave 10.1

column926:
08/Sep/25 3:08 PM;thomas.wermke@vodafone.com;Todays meeting with TechM and ACC-Team revealed that this issue is NO bug.
it is based more or less on a misunderstanding about the different PCAT setups for Telesales and Retail scenarios.

1. The purpose of the affected PCAT Compatibility Rule is to force an agent/user belonging to a Retail sales channel to select an sku from the category of retail blister(i.e. a SIM card item or eSIM cardboard card physically available in the shop).

2. During test execution, a clear distinction must be made between the agent’s affiliation with a particular sales channel and the login process on the respective Telesales or Retail websites.

3. Unfortunately the above mentioned rule cannot be restricted to the webite "Retail". Instead it evaluates the agent’s affiliation with a particular sales channel.

4. The current Prepaid product configuration in PCAT for Telesales restricts tariff selection to the predefined set of Telesales-specific SKUs (formatted as 'Kso' + <KIAS-TO-code>). Upon selection, a corresponding SIM/blister/item is automatically added to the shopping cart in a one-to-one relationship. Manual selection of alternative products or tariffs by the user is not permitted in this flow. After checkout, the order is transmitted to SAP, which initiates the dispatch of a pre-activated SIM card to the customer via mail.
 
5. The updated Prepaid product setup in PCAT for Retail enables the selection of both a blister item and a tariff from the available set of Retail tariffs (SKUs formatted as 'K' + <KIAS-TO-code>). Typically, the user first selects a blister item, after which a default tariff —usually the one printed on the packaging and defined in the KIAS table PREPAID_PACKAGE for the selected item_id— is automatically pre-selected. The user then has the option to deselect and change this default tariff and choose an alternative from the list of available tariffs, as defined in the KIAS table ACTIVATION_SETTINGS for the selected item_id. Upon checkout, the retail agent hands the blister/SIM to the customer, and the order is transmitted to the KIAS backend for subscriber activation. Especially in this scenario, it is important to use PCAT rules to force the user to select a blister and a tariff before checkout. 

-> Telesales user/sales id should belong to a Telesales channel (not the website) and a blister item is added automatically to the shopping cart after tariff selection.
Retail user/sales id should belong to a Retail channel (Filiale, Fachhandel, Partneragentur) and a tariff is preselected after blister selection.Manual choice of a blister is mandatory.

-> Tickets OS-77100, OS-76802, OS-76950 should be rejected and cancelled.;;;

Hi Ajay,

I checked further over code we are checking both OSE and Non OSE open orders to disable the Debit to Credit button.

*OSE open Order:* On OSE side if the customer don't have any order (Orders with status not equal to ‘{{{}SO_COMPLETED_SUCCESS{}}}, {{{}SO_COMPLETED_FAILED{}}}, {{{}SO_COMPLETED_WITH_CANCELLATION{}}}' and package with status not equal '{{{}OnHold-PendingOnlineIdentSignDoc{}}}, {{{}OnHold-PendingOnlineIdentification{}}}’ if all these conditions are met and results found then we treat it as OSE open Order)

*Non OSE Open Order:* If in mode logs we check if customer has any{{{}PendingOrder{}}}info node to decide on non ose open order.

If we don't find any results on both then we consider customer don't have an open order and Wechsel Debit to Credit button is enabled;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 10.1 | ACC2 | CR896 | OGW not suppressing  CustomerReaction service in the ContractSummarys sendDocument request for SOHO Cable KIP in Telesales channel with B2B _TELESALES_OL_ AGENT_NOCS role
column39:

7.Agent submit order
8.Verify senddocument request for Customer reaction field

column923:
02/Sep/25 7:11 PM;tasneem.sattar@vodafone.com;*Team PAPS Investigation Results* 

Mobile_Hardware file gets the data from two table

1- OPM_HARDWARE -> this for the data in the UI

2- PREP_HARDWARE -> AKA SAP HARDWARE, and this is for the SAP data

 

the table PREP_HARDWARE which contains the SAP data, it doesn't have a column called "Estimated_delivery_date" at all, so when we actually exporting the Sap data from prep hardware we set the value of the "Estimated_delivery_date" from the article No entity linked to this PREP hardware entity.

+*so, the "Estimated_delivery_date" can be empty in two cases*+

1- this sap hardware isn't linked to article no *(Not the case looking at the file)*

2- the article no linked to this sap hardware has an empty *Estimated_delivery_date* value

 

I ran a query on ACC to check the second case and it actually prove there are no values

column1: OSF | Wave10.1 | ACC2 | SIM Card type change when the backoffice agent retrieves the saved offer.
column39:
While performing Mobile D2C Save offer test case, We have observed, SIM Card type change when the backoffice agent retrieves the saved offer.

Sim-Kartentyp (SIM card type) as Nutzung bestehender SIM-Karte (Use of existing SIM card) is selected while capturing offer but when back office agent retrieves saved offer, Omnius is showing Sim-Kartentyp (SIM card type) as Physische SIM (Physical SIM).

Please find below screenshots:

!image-2025-08-28-00-02-40-754.png|width=501,height=196!

!image-2025-08-28-00-03-01-382.png|width=497,height=194!

 # Login to Omnius as Telesales Agent.
 # Search existing Mobile Prepaid Customer.
 # Clicks on D2C button.
 # Select Hardware and Tariff.
 # Proceed to checkout, Select New IBAN in Monthly payment section (Non-German IBAN).
 # Clicks on send to BO button (Offer is saved).
 # Go to Offer Manager and Retrieve offer.
 # Clicks on edit offer and verify new connection over data for SIM Card.

Actual: SIM Card type change when the backoffice agent retrieves the saved offer.

Expected: SIM Card type should be same when backoffice agent retrieves saved offer.

column367: Back-office Agent cannot see saved offer summary product.
column612:
Root Cause : The issue has come due to php upgradation. The error occurred because $values['endPeriod'] was an empty string, and PHP 8 does not allow arithmetic operations between a string and an integer.

In PHP 8, type handling is stricter. If $values['endPeriod'] is an empty string (''), subtracting an integer from it ('' - $monthDiff) is not allowed, resulting in a fatal error.




$result = (max(($values['endPeriod'] - $monthDiff), 0)) ?: $values['endPeriod'];
Fix: To resolve the issue, the value was explicitly cast to an integer before performing the subtraction.
We have delivered a full delivery  towards ACC2 for Wave10.1

Details will be available on https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OSFCICD-921

Please refer below table for all the details related to deliverables.

"... We discussed this topic with [@Markus Latos, Vodafone (External)|mailto:Markus.Latos@Vodafone.com] to align on required security measures for using BasicAuth as authentication method on interface level for handing over customers to the AgentDesktop. As outcome of this,  we aligned on the necessity to do a security assessment for the same to analyze the security impact in details  to decide on the required actions for productive use of this feature. column1: OSF || ACC Environments || Wave 10 || ACC1 & ACC3 | User accounts are facing ACCESS BLOCKED Issue
column39:
Hello Team

We are writing to report a recurring issue observed in the OSF ACC1/2/3 environments. Recently, users have been experiencing *ACCESS BLOCKED* errors. Even after activating the user accounts and resetting their passwords, the issue persists.

To address this, we are raising a defect so that your team can investigate and troubleshoot the root cause. This issue has been occurring consistently over the past few months.

As a temporary workaround, we are creating alternate user accounts for the requestors to ensure their tasks are not impacted.

We kindly request your team to investigate this issue and share your findings along with a resolution plan

Below are examples user accounts details those are facing ACCESS BLOCKED issues:
[harish.madipeddi1@vodafone.com|mailto:harish.madipeddi1@vodafone.com]
[yogesh.borade1@vodafone.com|mailto:yogesh.borade1@vodafone.com]

column1: OSF | W10.0, W10.0.2, W10.1 | ACC | VORAS SetOrderStatus response not update in OGW for Retail Mobile order
column39:
We have observed that for Mobile retail order  “SetOrderStatus” response not updated in OGW for mobile order  

*Test Data:*

Omnius_Order: 1230405
CS: 15485840

CD: 119049979

OGW_order_id: 3050800

 

*Steps to Reproduce-*
1. Login to retail channel
2. Select Mobile package
3. Select tariff Plan
4. Submit the order.

column1: OSF | Wave10.0 | ACC1 | Getting 503 internal server error while clicking  on green checkmark  after serial number validated in  Cable TV
column39:
Hello  Team,

We are trying to perform Cable TV flow. However, we are getting a 503 internal server error.

Steps to reproduce:
 # load a Cable TV address on ACC, e. g.: "Hagelstangestr. 30, 81927 München"
 # click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel TV" 
 # select a Basic TV container, e.g.: "[CHDC399] Vodafone Basic TV Cable"
 # click on "Hardware"
 # select "RCOWNHD"
 # enter a valid serial number, e. g.:  "93640638565255"
 # click on the button "Prüfen"
 # click on the green checkmark

Actual result: We are getting a {*}503 internal server error{*}.

!image-2025-08-22-12-49-57-487.png|width=374,height=201!
!image-2025-08-22-12-46-56-347.png|width=371,height=176!

 

Expected result: We should be able to proceed further after clicking on green check mark
column367: unable to proceed further to book Cable TV with Own Hardware
column612:
RCA:

There was a response structure mismatch in the GetTvEquipmentFeatures service. The OGW service returns SupportedSmartcardList[SupportedSmartcard], but in Vfde, we were referencing only SupportedSmartcardList. We missed validating the presence of the child node SupportedSmartcard.

column1: OSF | Wave10.1 | ACC2 | Omnius is allowing agent to proceed with the sales flow without entering a SIM number in the Main Card Physical SIM Textbox.
column39:
While performing Mobile Postpaid SOHO Private RV New Sim only Activation with MultiSIM in Retail channel, Omnius is allowing agent to proceed further without entering a SIM number in Physical SIM Textbox for main card which is leading order failure in KIAS with below error message:

Error Message: An error was encountered while invoking KIAS-ActivateSubscriber WS. Details [Error_Code: EAI004300, Error_Message: Serial Number is not provided., Error_Type: Functional, Error_Sevirity: E, Error_Information: SERIAL_NUMBER is not provided, Backend Error Code: 1907]

SKY Screenshot:

!image-2025-08-19-17-50-17-505.png|width=396,height=277!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Retail channel.
 # Create Mobile SOHO Private RV Package with SIM Only package.
 # Add one MultiSIM.
 # Proceed to checkout.
 # Select Physical SIM for Main Card.
 # Select ESIM for MultiSIM Card.
 # Clicks on Weiter without entering SIM Number in Main Card.

Actual: Omnius is allowing agent to proceed further without entering a SIM number in Main Card Physical SIM Textbox in case of Mobile New ACQ with MultiSIM for SOHO Private RV Customer type.

Expected: Omnius should not allow agent to proceed without entering SIM number.

Please find below screenshot:

!image-2025-08-19-17-01-18-042.png|width=331,height=172!

Note: Issue is observed only for SOHO Private RV customer type.

 #

column939:
08/Sep/25 3:04 PM;thomas.wermke@vodafone.com;Todays meeting with TechM and ACC-Team revealed that this issue is NO bug.
it is based more or less on a misunderstanding about the different PCAT setups for Telesales and Retail scenarios.

1. The purpose of the affected PCAT Compatibility Rule is to force an agent/user belonging to a Retail sales channel to select an sku from the category of retail blister(i.e. a SIM card item or eSIM cardboard card physically available in the shop).

2. During test execution, a clear distinction must be made between the agent’s affiliation with a particular sales channel and the login process on the respective Telesales or Retail websites.

3. Unfortunately the above mentioned rule cannot be restricted to the webite "Retail". Instead it evaluates the agent’s affiliation with a particular sales channel.

4. The current Prepaid product configuration in PCAT for Telesales restricts tariff selection to the predefined set of Telesales-specific SKUs (formatted as 'Kso' + <KIAS-TO-code>). Upon selection, a corresponding SIM/blister/item is automatically added to the shopping cart in a one-to-one relationship. Manual selection of alternative products or tariffs by the user is not permitted in this flow. After checkout, the order is transmitted to SAP, which initiates the dispatch of a pre-activated SIM card to the customer via mail.
 
5. The updated Prepaid product setup in PCAT for Retail enables the selection of both a blister item and a tariff from the available set of Retail tariffs (SKUs formatted as 'K' + <KIAS-TO-code>). Typically, the user first selects a blister item, after which a default tariff —usually the one printed on the packaging and defined in the KIAS table PREPAID_PACKAGE for the selected item_id— is automatically pre-selected. The user then has the option to deselect and change this default tariff and choose an alternative from the list of available tariffs, as defined in the KIAS table ACTIVATION_SETTINGS for the selected item_id. Upon checkout, the retail agent hands the blister/SIM to the customer, and the order is transmitted to the KIAS backend for subscriber activation. Especially in this scenario, it is important to use PCAT rules to force the user to select a blister and a tariff before checkout. 

-> Telesales user/sales id should belong to a Telesales channel (not the website) and a blister item is added automatically to the shopping cart after tariff selection.
Retail user/sales id should belong to a Retail channel (Filiale, Fachhandel, Partneragentur) and a tariff is preselected after blister selection.Manual choice of a blister is mandatory.

-> Tickets OS-77100, OS-76802, OS-76950 should be rejected and cancelled.;;;

column367: Agent not able to search Solstice customer
column612:
(Resolution) What was done to fix the issue?
The new Fabric target group Ip's registered and the old ones deregistered .

(Root Cause) What caused the issue?
The Target group ip were pointing to old ips , that cause the issue.

(Prevention) What preventive actions should be taken?
Register the new ip after any new node recreation activity will never cause this issue.

column1: ON-HOLD | OSF | Wave10.1 | ACC2 | CR860 - Implementation of Powers of attorney/Vollmachten documents
column39:
This is a tracking bug, related to the current implemetation of the different SW parts(OMNIUS, OGW, OouputManagement) for the RT document section of power of attorneys/Vollmachten.

 

Amdocs: FAST-832 CR860 - Implementation of authorisations to view contracts, amendments and for new contracts in Retail - Vodafone Global Jira

TechM: OAF-900 OMNIUS, SUBM : As an Agent, i wanted to send Vollmachten (Power Of Attorney) data in SubmitOrder, so that with powers of attorney case Agent can serve better to customer. - Vodafone Global Jira

TechM: OAF-901 OMNIUS, SUBM : As an OIL system, i wanted to do mapping and send Vollmachten (Power Of Attorney) attribute in ProcessOrder/SubmitOrder, so that with powers of attorney case Agent can serve better to customer. - Vodafone Global Jira

OM: 

!image-2025-08-07-21-59-59-934.png!
The OM change is part of BSS46 HF3.
Delivery of HF3 in test (PR) is planned for July 17.
After formal acceptance (RFI), HF3 will go live and be merged to BSS47/IT later (assuming there are no issues in PROD).
This would then be suitable for the planned OSF E2E test starting about mid of September with Wave10.1.
 

{color:#00875a}*+Current implemetation and test with W10.1:+*{color}
 
{*}{color:#00875a}First name, last name1, and date of birth{color}{*}: mandatory parameters
• TechM - implemented
• Amdocs/OGW - implemented
• OutputManagement - implemented
• {color:#00875a}*ACC test - E2E test with OM part in scope with W10.1*{color}
 
 
*+Not E2E implemented and also not in scope of W10.1:+*
 
{*}Salutation{*}: optional parameter
• TechM - not implemented or required with W10.1 (as soon as TechM implements the 'Salutation' field in the frontend, the E2E flow should work automatically and the salutation should be printed on the document).
• Amdocs/OGW - implemented in OGW for a later point of time . Currently only as a placeholder.
• OutputManagement - implemented
• ACC test with W10.1 - E2E test with OM part not in scope
 
{*}Last name2{*}: optional parameter
• TechM: implemented
• Amdocs/OGW - LastName2 appears in the OGW logs, but is NOT transferred to OM with the SendDocumentRequest.
{color:#de350b}-> In clarification with Thorsten L. and Andreas B. about the reason{color}

{color:#de350b}03.09: Feedback from Andreas/Thorsten: LastName2 should be transferred from OWG to OM. An improvement story for Amdocs will be created.{color}

• Output Management - implemented
• ACC test with W10.1 - E2E test with OM part not in scope
 
{*}LastName3{*}: optional parameter
• TechM: implemented
• Amdocs/OGW - LastName3 appears in the OGW logs, but is NOT transferred to OM with the SendDocumentRequest.
{color:#de350b}-> In clarification with Thorsten L. and Andreas B. about the reason{color}

{color:#de350b}03.09: Feedback from Andreas/Thorsten: LastName3 should be transferred from OWG to OM. An improvement story for Amdocs will be created.{color}
• Output Management: implemented
• ACC test with W10.1 - E2E test with OM part not in scope.

column1: On-Hold | SPN-OPT-000143071 | OSF | Wave10.0 | ACC1 | Retail | At a TV tariff change with analog change (KASWAP) with a Service option ONLY on the 2nd package the contract document is not created
column39:
Browser: Chrome

Channel: Retail

Cable PCAT version: V2510_2025_07_00_072

Test customer: 935320753 (TV tariff change allowed and analog product will be changed as well and SN3 in the inventory)

 

*Please note:*

1. if we have only 1 TV package then the Contract Document is opened

!image-2025-07-15-14-23-41-071.png!

!image-2025-07-15-14-23-21-439.png!

2. If we create a new activation with KIP and TV, we also have 2 packages, but here the contract document can also be opened

!image-2025-07-15-14-34-07-549.png!

!image-2025-07-15-14-34-40-899.png!

 

+Actual Result:+ At a TV tariff change with analog change (KASWAP) {*}and on the 2nd package ONLY the service option (SN3/ SN4) stays in the inventory{*}, Contract document is stuck at SPP state in OM

+Expected Result:+ At a TV tariff change with analog change (KASWAP) it should be possible to open the contract document

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * load a Cable TV customer in Retail, e. g.: 935320753 
 * click on "Meine Produkte >> KAD package >> Paket ändern" 
 * select a new TV tariff, e.g.: "[CTWGPNTW1] Vodafone GigaTV Home Cable inklusive Netflix"

        – > "KASWAP" is preselected automatically – > *OK*

!image-2025-07-15-13-56-42-102.png!
 * select a new analog product where ONLY "SN3" will be kept in the 2nd package, e. g.: "[TCM:TW1] Vodafone TV Connect Standard"
 * click on the button "Weiter"
 * click on the button "Zum Checkout"
 * continue with the order until the Contract Summary page
 * click on the button "Drucken"

– > Contract Summary is opened – > *OK*
 * select the checkbox " Die Vertragszusammenfassung wurde besprochen und über SignoSign abgeschlossen"
 * click on the button "Weiter"
 * click on the button "Drucken"

– > Contract Document is NOT opened – > *NOT OK*

*!image-2025-07-15-14-02-17-123.png!*

23/Jul/25 8:45 PM;alka.kshirsagar2@vodafone.com;SPN-OPT-000143071 is rejected with below comment:

Hi [Hamza Balci, Vodafone (External)|https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hamza.balci1%40vodafone.com] 

wir haben [OMART-466|https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fde.jira.agile.vodafone.com%2Fbrowse%2FOMART-466&data=05%7C02%7Cnorbert.forai%40dxc.com%7Cd624ef0bfba24639d87208ddc6027487%7C93f33571550f43cfb09fcd331338d086%7C0%7C0%7C638884436496987768%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&sdata=7%2Fh9LoRc%2BK8CfdKGLgws8si%2BqhXqbJgAKG2sbeLrgf0%3D&reserved=0] weiter untersucht und festgestellt, dass die Ursache des Problems darin liegt, dass in der zweiten „PackageConfiguration” vom Typ TV der Knoten „CommercialProducts“ fehlt.

Laut omogw.xsd sollte unter einem PackageConfiguration Knoten mindestens ein Knoten „CommercialProducts“ vorhanden sein.

!image-2025-07-23-20-45-15-966.png!

Sobald mindestens ein Knoten „CommercialProducts“ hinzugefügt wurde, treten keine Probleme bei der Verarbeitung auf (siehe Anhang).

*Wir haben auch die Testdaten überprüft, die dem Produktionsvorfall INC000094827316 beigefügt waren. Dort besteht das gleiche Problem.*

*Da es sich um ein Problem mit den Eingabedaten handelt, sollte im Eingabesystem geprüft werden, warum das System diese Informationen in diesem Szenario nicht an OM weiterleitet.*

FYI: die zweite PackageConfiguration  Knoten kann entfernt werden. Es funktioniert ebenfalls einwandfrei, sofern die erste PackageConfiguration  für TV die aktuellen Details nach der Änderung enthält.

 

Gruß,

Norbert Forai;;;

column927:
25/Jul/25 5:37 PM;affan.baragazi@vodafone.com;Hi [~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com] ,

OGW includes *CommercialProducts* in a package only when the *LineActivityType* in the *CommercialDetails* (received in the SubmitOrder request from Omnius) is not "{*}REFUSE{*}" or "{*}DROP{*}", and the *ScopeList* contains a Scope with the value "{*}Contract{*}".

For the second package, such CommercialDetails are missing, which is why OGW does not add any CommercialProducts to it.

PFB for reference:
An example from the second package where CommercialProducts are not mapped:

column1: OSF | ACC1 | Wave10.0 | Performance Defect | Response time degradation observed for Retrieve Customer Transaction
column39:
Observed response time degradation for Retrieve Customer transaction.
Steps to reproduce:
 # Launch ACC1 env.
 # Login
 # Customer Search
 # Retrieve Customer

[W10.0 OSF Performance Test Reports - VOIS - OSF - Vodafone Global Confluence|https://confluence.sp.vodafone.com/display/OF/W10.0+OSF+Performance+Test+Reports+-+VOIS]
column367:
The identified performance defect in Wave 10.0 (Retrieve Customer Transaction) is causing significant response time degradation across critical customer-facing transactions in the ACC1 environment. These delays directly impact the end-user experience during high-volume operations.
If unresolved, these issues risk breaching SLAs for transaction processing and may delay the planned go-live for Wave 10.0, impacting both customer satisfaction and operational KPIs.

column1: OSF | Wave 10.0 | ACC1 | CR887 | Some UME cancellation reasons are not displayed in OM under ''Details Ergänzungen''
column39:
*This is a Tracking ticket, ACC1/test2b*

When an OSF Unity order is cancelled(storniert) in Unity backend RNS, some cancellation reasins are not displayed in OM under ''Details Ergänzungen''

*Steps to reproduce:*

1) Check Servicibilty with valid UM Address in Telases/Retail
2) Select UM package and proceed to Configurator
3) Fill all the necessary customer details and Submit the order
4) Cancel the OSF order in UM Backend with reason 'STORNO VORVERMARKTUNG'
5) Check the display of the 'Details Ergänzungen' in Order Manager

*Actual Result:*
Cancellation Reason 'Storno Vorvermarktung' ist NOT shown under 'Details Ergänzungen' in Order Manager:

RNS

!image-2025-06-05-10-51-55-264.png|width=706,height=397!

 

OM

!image-2025-06-05-10-54-47-161.png|width=885,height=426!


WID - (K) WIDERRUF
SVM - (S) STORNO VORVERMARKTUNG
PZT - (K) PRODUKT ZU TEUER
FAD - (K) FALSCHE ADRESSE

 


*Expected Result:*

Cancellation Reason 'Storno Vorvermarktung' ist shown under 'Details Ergänzungen' in Order Manager.

column920:
06/Jun/25 5:36 PM;nina.pickl@vodafone.com;[~anton.ustimenko@vodafone.com] , also VKD is involved, Unity can only communicate with OSF via VKD.

The flow is as follow:  cancellation reason ist trasferred from Unity vo VDK, afterwards VKD is trasferring the reason to OGW/OSF.

If OSF  is not getting the Info from VKD, the reason can not be displayed in OSF.

So the issue is between Unity and VKD and this change was already tested from your side. You can create a Defect against Unity, related to this test task: [[QA] OSF/VKD Gateway/Minerva Adapter - Adjustments Order Manager - Portals - Vodafone DE Confluence|https://de.confluence.agile.vodafone.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=599719049];;;
column921:
06/Jun/25 6:39 PM;anton.ustimenko@vodafone.com;Ok. I'll double check it - maybe you're right. 

This feature is actually: [[DISPYRAMID-217] Adapt VKDGateway to pass through new order details - DE Jira|https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/DISPYRAMID-217] should implement this.

Just for your understanding the root cause:

the cancellation as self seems to be working fine and this is working without Portals systems. RNS communicate in this case directly with OSF systems.

By displaying of information in OM the OSF accessing MinervaAdapter via VkdGateway. And here is probably the issue. I addressed it to team Pyramid as they implemented the extension for cancellation codes in April release 2025. 

 

 ;;;

column925:
13/Jun/25 12:10 PM;atharva.paskanthi@vodafone.com;*Update on PSTBUG*
*Ahmed ElZahaby, Vodafone (Team Pyramid) added a comment -*

I've looked in it, it seems like it's caused because the declined reason isn't founded in the enums that defined in StatusDetails in UnityOrderTracker, so the flow here we 've created an isCancellationReason:

https://webgit.kabeldeutschland.de/projects/LUAAUTO/repos/unityordertracker/browse/UnityOrderTrackerScheduler/src/main/java/com/vodafone/cable/uotracker/updater/data/StatusDetail.java#254-256

That function checks if the order status that returned from MinervaAdaptor exists in CANCELLATION_REASON_MAP value and if it's not it set it with null:

https://webgit.kabeldeutschland.de/projects/LUAAUTO/repos/unityordertracker/browse/UnityOrderTrackerScheduler/src/main/java/com/vodafone/cable/uotracker/updater/vkdgateway/VkdGatewayOrderStatusUpdater.java?at=24d5d4b6d127bf5feee0bb99d80f3f74a73fc7df#63-66

And after I've search for the provided cancellation reason ''STORNO VORVERMARKTUNG'' ('CANCELLATION PRE-MARKETING') I didn't find it in the CANCELLATION_REASON_MAP values.

So, my suggested solution here if the team who is ever responsible for UnityOrderTracker just need to add that cancellation reason into the enums it has in StatusDetails.;;;

30/Jun/25 8:01 PM;nina.pickl@vodafone.com;[~anton.ustimenko@vodafone.com]

We found the place in the VKD logs, where the cancellation reason=cancellation eventCode should be present, but it is missing.

Means the value of the Order Manager field "STATUS_DETAIL" is NOT present in the VKD Gateway logs for SOME cancellation reasons.

*Unity is not sending this code via Minera to VKD.* 

Like discussed in the beginning, someone from Cable team should create a Bug for Minerva and Unity team can check the cancellations reasons code table again.

The Unity change was implemented an year ago, maybe in the meantime some new cancellation reasons were added and they the table should now be updated.

 

VKD Log for the NOT working cancellation reason ‚Storno Vorvermarktung':

 

"statusInfos" : [#012    \{#012      "statusType" : "VALUE",#012      "system" : "cable",#012    "eventCode" : "CUSTOMER_ID",#012      "eventPresentationText" : "new cable customer id 173663507",#012      "eventValue" : "173663507"#012    }#  +*{color:#de350b}***MISSING PART***{color}*+

 

As example, for other reasons like 'double order', the value is present in the logs and it is also trasferregd from VKD to OSF, is working fine:

 

"statusInfos" : [#012    \{#012      "statusType" : "VALUE",#012      "system" : "cable",#012      "eventCode" : "CUSTOMER_ID",#012      "eventPresentationText" : "new cable customer id 566519401",#012      "eventValue" : "566519401"#012    },#012    {#012      "statusType" : "EVENT_DETAIL",#012      +{color:#00875a}*"eventCode" : "UXDU"#012*{color}+    }#012  ]#012};;;
